    <title>Posting from O2 mobile to Facebook using  http://www.facebook.com/connect/prompt_feed.php endpoint is bloken</title>
    <description>
        <paragraph id="1">
            <sentence id="1.1">Created an attachment (id=1742)
Screenshot</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="2">
            <sentence id="2.1">Please note: I am in the process of developing mobile web connect with publishing to facebook using  http://www.facebook.com/connect/prompt_feed.php endpoint.</sentence>
            <sentence id="2.2">My implementation uses exact same workflow as the Facebook s mobile sample application The Run Around and the symptoms are the same.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="3">
            <sentence id="3.1">Attempts to post to facebook from mobile phones through O2 (http://www.o2.co.uk/) 3G network always fail.</sentence>
            <sentence id="3.2">Note that this is specific to O2.</sentence>
            <sentence id="3.3">Publishing from phones through other mobile providers networks work as expected.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="4">
            <sentence id="4.1">Repro steps:</sentence>
            <sentence id="4.2">1 Using any O2 phone with web browser over O2 3G connection_ navigate to http://itsti.me;</sentence>
            <sentence id="4.3">2 Click  Connect with Facebook  link;</sentence>
            <sentence id="4.4">3 Provide facebook credentials if needed;</sentence>
            <sentence id="4.5">4 Once logged in to The Run Around_ try to log a new run;</sentence>
            <sentence id="4.6">5 Make sure that Post on Facebook checkbox is checked and click Add Run button;</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="5">
            <sentence id="5.1">Expected:</sentence>
            <sentence id="5.2">* Connect with Facebook form to appear_ allowing to publish story;</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="6">
            <sentence id="6.1">Actual:</sentence>
            <sentence id="6.2">* Facebook Login form appears.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="7">
            <sentence id="7.1">See attached 1-Posting-On-Facebook.</sentence>
            <sentence id="7.2">png (It seems that at this point_ facebook does not recognized logged in user / session - this is wrong);</sentence>
            <sentence id="7.3">* Logging in with facebook credentials result in one of the following:</sentence>
            <sentence id="7.4">* Timeout;</sentence>
            <sentence id="7.5">* HTTP 504.</sentence>
            <sentence id="7.6">See attached 5-Posting-On-Facebook_HTTP504.</sentence>
            <sentence id="7.7">png</sentence>
            <sentence id="7.8">* Cookies Required error.</sentence>
            <sentence id="7.9">See attached 6-Posting-On-Facebook_Cookies.</sentence>
            <sentence id="7.10">png</sentence>
        </paragraph>
